Sentencas: In this work, slurry spraying is evaluated as a deposition method of thin electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: FABRICATION AND CHARACTERIZATION OF ANODE SUPPORTED SOLID OXIDE FUEL CELLS

Sentencas: This method is cost effective, uncomplicated and have several advantages in respect to widely used screen printing method.
Titulo: FABRICATION AND CHARACTERIZATION OF ANODE SUPPORTED SOLID OXIDE FUEL CELLS

Sentencas: Influence of deposition parameters: slurry concentration, spraying pressure are discussed.
Titulo: FABRICATION AND CHARACTERIZATION OF ANODE SUPPORTED SOLID OXIDE FUEL CELLS

Sentencas: Anode supported cells are produced with three different electrolyte thicknesses: 5, 10 and 20 mu m showing flexibility of the developed method.
Titulo: FABRICATION AND CHARACTERIZATION OF ANODE SUPPORTED SOLID OXIDE FUEL CELLS

Sentencas: Prepared fuel cells achieve satisfactory power densities of almost 1 W cm(-2) at 800 degrees C. As evidenced by impedance spectroscopy, performance of cells is determined by the polarization resistance.
Titulo: FABRICATION AND CHARACTERIZATION OF ANODE SUPPORTED SOLID OXIDE FUEL CELLS

Sentencas: Cross sections of cells show that all electrolyte layers are of high quality.
Titulo: FABRICATION AND CHARACTERIZATION OF ANODE SUPPORTED SOLID OXIDE FUEL CELLS

Sentencas: Slurry spraying is a feasible method for fabrication of functional cells and can be easily scaled for large quantity production.
Titulo: FABRICATION AND CHARACTERIZATION OF ANODE SUPPORTED SOLID OXIDE FUEL CELLS
